				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">A lot of the time it's sensible to just store a score in decimal, rather than as a binary number that you'd have to convert, i.e. just store the 7 digit score as 7 bytes (each value 0-10) and write a routine that will add points to it (carrying anything that overflows 10 to the next one).</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

